1) Definitions
- “CLP” means the Constitutional Language Protocol used to author and operate governance scripts/artifacts.
- “CLP-Compliant Use” means: (a) the Software is used in a manner consistent with CLP requirements documented in CLP.md,
  and (b) the user does not remove or bypass governance controls intended to preserve auditability, append-only integrity,
  or SIM vs REAL enforcement boundaries.
- “Commercial Use” means use primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

